    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Square-back Windsor chairs with a turned cross piece framed at the top of the back posts and accompanied by one or two horizontal cross slats at mid-back and sometimes with short spindles between the seat and lower slat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000014271/Evans, American Windsor Furniture (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sillas Windsor de respaldo cuadrado con una pieza cruzada torneada en la parte superior de los postes del respaldo y acompañada por una o dos tablillas cruzadas horizontales al medio del respaldo y a veces con husillos cortos entre el asiento y la tablilla inferior.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Square-back Windsorstoelen met een gedraaide dwarsverbinding  bovenop de achterstijlen en één of twee horizontale dwarslatten midden in de rug. Soms hebben ze korte spijlen tussen de zitting en de onderste dwarslat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>方形椅背的溫莎椅，椅背柱上方橫貫著車削過的木桿，椅背中段為附帶著一或兩道水平的交叉式椅背橫木，部份在較低的椅背橫木和椅座之間會裝有數根紡錘狀短木軸。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
